releases.body:
# Changes
- Added command groups, so that help text can show related commands together.  When initializing the `ArgParser`, you can pass an array of command groups (excerpt from `examples/basic.zig`:
```zig
.groups = &.{
  .{  
    .name = "Spells",
    .description = "Magical incantations and evocations.",
    .commands = &.{ 
      .{  
        .name = "transmogrify",
        .opts = &.{
          .{ 
            .longName = "into", 
            .shortName = "i", 
              .description = "[...]", .maxNumParams = 1 },
            .{ .longName = "another", .description = "Another option for the command." },
        }
      },
      .{  
        .name = "lightning_bolt", 
        .description = "Creates a blistering bolt of lightning!.",
      },
    },
  },
  .{  
    .name = "Production",
    .description = "Create new magical implements.",
    .commands = &.{ 
      .{
        .name = "brew_potion",
        .description = "Creates a new potion",
      },
      .{
        .name = "write_scroll",
        .description = "Creates a new scroll.",
      },
    },
  },
}
```
- Added checking for ANSI color support on stdout to the printer module.
- Added the ability to set an option with no parameters, a single parameter or multiple parameters by default with the `DefaultValue`  EnumUnion.

```zig
var parser = try zargs.ArgParser.init(std.heap.page_allocator, .{ .name = "Default options", .opts = &.{
  .{ .longName = "beta", .shortName = "b", .description = "", .default = zargs.DefaultValue.set() },
  .{ .longName = "gamma", .shortName = "g", .description = "", .default = zargs.DefaultValue.param("blah") },
  .{ .longName = "delta", .shortName = "d", .description = "", .default = zargs.DefaultValue.params(&.{ "boop", "blop", "bleep" }) },
} });
```

- Added ability to prepend `no-` to an option to unset it for the case of a value being default set that a user wants to unset.  For example, you could have an option `stack-trace` that defaults to set, and a user can pass `--no-stack-trace`.
- Added min/max positional args configuration, description for positional args and possible default value, also via `DefaultValue` EnumUnion.
- Added helper methods to `ArgParserResult` to get the (first) parameter of an option result back: `optionValOrDefault`, `optionNumVal`, `optionNumValOrDefault`.
- Added ability to stack multiple options, increasing their count.  This allows for things like `-vvv` where the option `v` would show as having occurred 3 times.
```zig
.{
  .longName = "verbose",
  .shortName = "v",
  .description = "log verbosity",
  .maxOccurences = 5,
  .maxNumParams = 0,
}
```
  Stacked options can be mixed, and the last in the set is also able to receive parameters.  So `-vs` for a `v` and `s` option, or `-vsf temp` for `v`, `s`, and `f` with the parameter `temp`.
